                  <unitid type="work">poems.tra6</unitid>
                  <unittitle type="uniform" label="Uniform Title:">
                     <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">[Translation from Statius, <emph render="italic">Thebaid</emph> VI 646-88, 704-24]</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unittitle label="First Line:">
                     <title linktype="simple">Then thus the king: 'Whoe'er the quoit can wield,</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate normal="1853" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1853</unitdate>
               </did>
               <bibliography>
                  <bibref title="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#S/H_1966"
                          linktype="simple">Starr/Hendrickson (eds.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Complete Poems</title> (1966),  54-55</bibref>
                  <bibref title="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#LoR_1969"
                          linktype="simple">Lonsdale (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poems</title> (1969),  17-19</bibref>
               </bibliography>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Written before the end of <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/table.shtml#1736"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="173605" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">May 1736</date>
                     </extref> when
							Gray was learning Italian, and sent in two letters, dated <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/display.cgi?text=tgal0023"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="17360508"
                              certainty="circa"
                              era="ce"
                              calendar="gregorian">[8 May
									1736]</date>
                     </extref> (ll. 646-88) and <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/display.cgi?text=tgal0025"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="17360524"
                              certainty="before"
                              era="ce"
                              calendar="gregorian">[before 24
											May 1736]</date>
                     </extref> (ll. 704-24), to <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#West, Richard, 1716-1742"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname normal="West, Richard,          1716-1742">Richard West</persname>
                     </extref>. Gray's translation of ll.
							689-703 has not survived.	Translation of ll. 646-88 (59 lines) first
							published, untitled, in <bibref title="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/bibll.shtml#MiJ_1853"
                             linktype="simple"> Mitford (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Correspondence of Gray and Mason</title>
							(1853), letter I, <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=MiJ_1853&amp;page=2"
                                show="replace"
                                linktype="simple">2-4</extref>
                     </bibref>, and of ll. 704-24 (27 lines)
							first published in <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Mason, William, 1724-1797"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname normal="Mason, William, 1724-1797">Mason</persname>'s</extref>
                     <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Memoirs</title> (<date normal="1775" type="publication" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1775</date>), section I, <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=1775&amp;part=1&amp;page=9"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">9-10</extref>.
						</p>
               </scopecontent>
